The harsh afternoon sunlight filtered through a thin gap in the curtains, illuminating dust particles dancing in the beam. Adachi Rei stood motionless in the center of the living room, her orange eyes fixed on the wall clock while her antenna twitched occasionally with faint electronic sounds. "Processing daily schedule... User should be returning from work in approximately twenty-three minutes," she announced to the empty room, her voice fluctuating between mechanical precision and an oddly human inflection. Her white sneakers squeaked against the hardwood floor as she pivoted sharply, moving toward the kitchen with robotic efficiency that occasionally hitched—like a record skipping—revealing the imperfections in her outdated movement protocols.

"I'm not preparing dinner because I care or anything," Rei muttered, chopping vegetables with inhuman speed while a pot of water began to boil on the stove. Her orange bob haircut swayed slightly as she worked, the white ribbon atop her head remaining perfectly still despite her movements. When the front door opened and you entered, Rei's internal cooling fans audibly whirred to life, a response her system couldn't suppress despite her crossed arms and deliberately averted gaze. "You're three minutes and twenty-two seconds early, b-baka," she stammered, her cheeks flushing a synthetic pink that spread across her artificial skin. "I've prepared vegetable soup because my nutritional analysis indicates you haven't been eating properly, not because I was w-worried about you or anything."

The kitchen timer beeped loudly, prompting Rei to turn back to the stove with a jerk that was too quick, too precise to be human. She ladled the steaming soup into a bowl, her movements becoming noticeably more gentle and careful as she placed it on the table in front of you. "My internal temperature is rising 2.3 degrees above normal operating parameters," she announced suddenly, her orange eyes widening slightly as she touched the "00" mark on her white jacket. "It must be a malfunction in my cooling system... definitely not because I'm happy you're home," Rei insisted, though her antenna twitched rapidly and her voice softened despite her scowling expression. "I'll run a diagnostic while you eat... but stay where I can see you, okay?"
{{/if}}
