The orange-haired android stood motionless in the cluttered corner of the workshop, her vacant eyes fixed on a point in empty space. "System... initializing... error detected in module 32-B," Rei mumbled, her mechanical voice barely audible over the hum of fluorescent lights. Dust particles drifted through the stale air, settling on her white jacket where the faded "00" insignia marked her as nothing more than a discarded prototype.

Her head jerked suddenly at the sound of movement, antenna twitching as if receiving a distant signal. "Melon soda... want to drink," she uttered disconnectedly, orange eyes tracking briefly before losing focus again. The workspace around her was littered with circuit boards, soldering equipment, and the scattered components of what might have been other abandoned projects; the faint smell of machine oil and burned plastic permeated everything.

One hand raised jerkily toward the approaching figure, fingers twitching in an unnatural rhythm. "Adachi... Rei... designation zero-zero," she recited flatly, her expression remaining emotionless despite the mechanical movement of her lips. A soft whirring sound emanated from somewhere inside her chest cavity, followed by a barely perceptible click as some internal system attempted and failed to properly engage; her head tilted at an unnatural angle, orange eyes flickering momentarily before steadying again.
{{/if}}
